cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for binary classification using one-class classifiers based on non-parametric models, N-ary Trees and Minimum Spanning Trees class descriptors (MST-CD). These methods are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper's focus on classification and modelling of class descriptions also suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of pattern recognition (cs.PR) or information retrieval (cs.IR). However, given the emphasis on machine learning and computer vision, we consider cs.LG and cs.CV to be the most likely sub-categories.
